news.title: Finance ministry seeks details of property transactions above Rs 50 lakh
news.para: Officials from the state property registration department have confirmed the directions from the Union finance ministry and said that it was part of an "administrative" exercise and instructions have been given to all the sub-registrars.

news.title: Jharkhand prepares draft plan to regularize unauthorized residential buildings
news.para: "Chief minister Hemant Soren as minister of the department has given his nod to the 'Plan-2022' to regularize the unauthorized residential building in urban areas. The process of giving benefit of it to the people will be initiated soon," the statement said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body sets property tax target of Rs 400 crore for FY23
news.para: The tax flow took a beating due to the then highly prevailing Covid-19 pandemic in 2019-20 and 2020-21. The GVMC, for the first time, realised over ₹300 crore in the 2021-22. The GVMC wants to further boost its revenue collections this year.

news.title: Masterplan for Hosur new town development ready
news.para: According to officials, the government issued orders in 1984 for a new town development plan that was to cover 57 villages. Now the consent has been given for the plan which includes around 130 villages covering 734sqkm.

news.title: NGT's stay on 25,000 sq meter CRZ plot sale in Nerul to continue
news.para: The petitioners challenged the plot sale, pointing out that it violates the coastal regulation zone provisions as a third of the area falls under CRZ1 and a similar area is CRZ-ll.

news.title: Mumbai: 388 Mhada buildings set to get redevelopment push before BMC poll
news.para: Officials said that the Shinde-Fadnavis government is given an in-principle nod to redevelop these old buildings under section 33 (7) of the Development Control Regulation (DCR) with a floor space index (FSI) of 3 or additional incentive FSI of minimum 78%.

news.title: Time frame set for sanctioning domestic rooftop solar system in Tangedco
news.para: “The entire process of issuing technical feasibility has to be completed within a time frame of 15 days from the date of payment by the applicant,” reads the circular.

news.title: Chandigarh admin yet to decide on converting CHB leasehold properties to freehold
news.para: The CHB has once again approached the administration on the issue, listing the number of properties that could be converted from leasehold to freehold.

news.title: Trichy corporation begins poster drive against big property tax defaulters
news.para: Officials said that around 500 properties have been identified for putting up notices, mostly properties in zone I and III.

news.title: Existing home sales in U.S. drop 5.9% in October 2022
news.para: House resales, which account for a big chunk of U.S. home sales, slumped 28.4% on a year-on-year basis in October. That was the largest drop since February 2008.

news.title: NCLAT stays insolvency proceedings against BPTP
news.para: ​On November 14, the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) had directed to initiate insolvency proceedings against BPTP Ltd, a leading real estate player in Delhi-NCR, on a petition filed by an operational creditor, RBCL Projects.

news.title: Delhi: Metropolis Lab's MD buys Sunder Nagar bungalow for Rs 64 crore
news.para: Shah has paid Rs 2.56 crore stamp duty for the registration of the property. According to documents accessed by CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, Star hotel PVR Ltd has sold the bungalow and property has been registered on October 31.

news.title: Housing societies will need norms for EV charging, says Bombay HC
news.para: The petition contents that the charging time for EVs is between 3 hours and 30 hours and hence it becomes imperative for the owner of such vehicles to have access to charging infrastructure at their residence where they can charge their electric vehicles overnight or during weekends.

news.title: GVMC plans to develop model slum in each zone of Visakhapatnam
news.para: The GVMC will conduct a survey to understand the infrastructural matrix in these slums related to engineering, sewerage, water supply, town planning, sanitation, etc. and address them on a priority basis.

news.title: Two Bengaluru metro phase III corridors get government's in-principle nod
news.para: Phase 3 consists of 44.6km with two corridors: JP Nagar 4th Phase-Kempapura along ORR West (32.1km) and Hosahalli-Kadabagere along Magadi Road (12.5km).
